Now was the emphasis you felt like when you were 
there a large animal? Oh yeah, definitely. You

12:42.374 --> 12:47.401
didn't have much... No, you couldn't get in if you 
wanted to be a small animal. I intended to be a large

12:47.421 --> 12:52.109
animal too with my agricultural background. It 
was easy to do that. So you finished in 49 and then

12:56.315 --> 13:00.021
what did you do? I looked around for various places 
to practice and I ended up in Longview, Texas.

13:07.250 --> 13:09.512
setting up a mixed practice. By yourself? Yes, new 
practice. And how'd that work? It worked fine. I

13:17.319 --> 13:29.670
had all I could do and was at the point of having to 
hire another veterinarian when I decided that

13:17.319 --> 13:29.670
maybe I'd sell and come to West Texas. We were, my 
wife's in North Dakota and I was West Texas, and

13:36.528 --> 13:40.154
East Texas is different. I was very successful 
there and sold my practice. Had it on the market

13:45.642 --> 13:47.185
three days. Is that right? Yeah. Now you had an 
edge, it strikes me, maybe on some of these other

13:50.690 --> 13:56.679
people, because you had a lot of economics 
background. You bet I did. I made all of that. And

13:59.344 --> 14:03.430
you know, this is a question I ask all these people. 
What was your business? Because I see the practice

14:06.530 --> 14:09.374
of veterinary medicine as a business. Oh, it is. 
And apparently that's one of the real

14:10.596 --> 14:13.980
deficiencies that a lot of these people have had. 
