allowed you to go into areas that you couldn't go

16:11.383 --> 16:27.002
into otherwise.

16:30.222 --> 16:35.968
Now, has this been a continual problem for the 
practice, that is, your zoning problem? See, we

16:36.008 --> 16:42.434
are criticized for noise, barking, and for odors. 
It's been a real problem down through the years.

16:48.620 --> 16:58.710
And St. Louis

16:48.620 --> 16:58.710
formed a, not a resolution, a law, a zoning law, 
formed a new zoning law that allowed the

16:59.500 --> 17:09.711
veterinarians to go in with pretty much a closed 
building. And that made all the difference in the

17:09.731 --> 17:12.594
world. Because you were accepted, if you followed 
that one, two or three zones that you couldn't have

17:12.614 --> 17:20.922
gone in otherwise. And you could go in residential 
areas that are close to residential areas, which

17:21.583 --> 17:28.090
you needed to be. Has that been pretty well adopted 
now? Yeah, so it's universal. But it came out of St.

17:32.207 --> 17:33.428
Louis? Yes, and it came out about 51, 52,

17:33.448 --> 17:45.901
about 52, 53, something like that. Most everybody 
knows that. There was one guy named Bill. Two

17:50.886 --> 17:58.093
hospitals in Fort Worth just before I came and 
